tweet: In spite of all the obstacles that the COVID-19 outbreak had put in CT voters' way, that didn't stop them from turning out in record numbers. CT voters made their voices heard, no matter how different or challenging 2020 was!

tweet: Polling places were still open, operating with safety measures like plastic barriers between voters and volunteers, and spaced out voting booths. The typically long lines looked even longer to make enough space for people to wait to vote safely.
